  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2019-04-29",
    "date": "2020-06-22T13:47:47Z",
    "text": "Support Tools to Obliterate Pesky Robocalls Act or the STOP Robocalls Act\n\nThis bill provides measures to eliminate unlawful robocalls.\n\nSpecifically, the bill requires the Federal Communications Commission (FCC) to establish a streamlined process whereby a private entity may voluntarily share information about unlawful robocalls or text messages and unlawful caller identification spoofing. In addition, the bill authorizes a telecommunications company to provide a free, opt-in robocall blocking service to its customers.\n\nThe FCC must also study and report on whether a Voice Over Internet Protocol service should be required to provide the FCC with its contact information and retain records of all calls transmitted over the service."
  },
